--------------------------------------------------------------
Compiling and Running Rapid Prototype:
--------------------------------------------------------------


-The prototype is ran on the command line. 
-It can be ran on any CCIS Linux machines. 
-The prototype input takes two files. 
-A file can be a file in WAVE or MP3 format 
or a folder containing files in the WAVE or MP3 format


On a CCIS Linux Machine:


1. Open the command line. 


2. cd into our project directory containing the executable, 
named src:


$ cd src


4. Execute the following command:


$ ./p4500 -f <name> -f <name>

- Enter either -f for WAV/MP3 file, 
or -d for a directory containing the WAV/MP3 files.
- <name> is the path of the directory or file that already exists.


--------------------------------------------------------------
Third Party Software Used:
